title.rendered: Trent vs Welsh, English Men’s 100 League:  Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Pitch Report for Trent vs Welsh

1st innings average score: 149

2nd innings average score: 143

Type: Good for batting in both innings.

Time: August 29, 11:30 PM IST

Probable Playing XIS for Trent & Welsh

Probable XI for Trent: Alex Hales, Dawid Malan, Colin Munro, Tom Kohler-Cadmore (wk), Tom Moores, Lewis Gregory (c), Samit Patel, Daniel Sams, Luke Wood, Sam Cook, Tabraiz Shamsi

Probable XI for Welsh: Joe Clarke (wk), Tom Banton, Ben Duckett, David Miller, Dwaine Pretorius, Josh Cobb (c), Leus du Plooy, Matthew Critchley, Ish Sodhi, David Payne, Jake Ball

Game Changers

If not with the ball, Samit Patel offers points with the bat. He was promoted to No.4 in Trent’s last game, and he replied with a knock of 21 off 15 including two sixes. His eight wickets are the second-most for his team.

Dwaine Pretorius’ entry in the 100 League has reaped benefits for the fantasy players in all departments. He has hunted down four wickets. His scores down the order read 4*, 29, 15, and 23. And in the field, he has grabbed three catches.

Daniel Sams’ numbers, however, read slightly better in the business of all-rounders: six wickets, the highest score of 55*, and three catches.

Also Read:

Bangladesh vs Afghanistan, Asia Cup 2022 Fantasy Picks

How to save yourself from losing money during a fantasy cricket match?

Smart Fantasy Picks

In the list of wicketkeepers, Tom Kohler-Cadmore has outperformed his namesake Banton. Kohler-Cadmore has top scores of 41 and 30, and with the gloves, he has inflicted one stumping and taken three catches.

Luke Wood has scalped the bulk of the wickets for Trent. His nine wickets have come at a strike rate 15 and his best figures read 3 for 17.

On the other hand, Jake Ball has been the best bowler for Welsh. His best figures read 4 for 29, courtesy his ability to outfox the batters at the death with his variations.

Colin Munro has scored a twenty, thirty, and a fifty. He may not have been as consistent as he is expected to, but he has been getting good starts and hence justifying his selection percentage in fantasy cricket.

Power Players

Amongst both teams, Dawid Malan has generated the most fantasy points (210) on My11Circle. With 300 runs at a strike rate of 175, he is the season’s highest run-scorer. He has smashed three fifties and a thirty.

Alex Hales is not too far behind, with 181.5 points to his credit. Along with his batting talent (two fifties and two thirties), he has pouched points in the field as well. His five catches are the most by a Trent player.

For Welsh, Ben Duckett has been the best performer in fantasy leagues. He has scored 195 runs at an average of 33 and a strike rate of 138. He has also provided additional points for three catches.

Fantasy Tip of The Day

Picking all-rounders and death bowlers have been keeping fantasy players in the game in this season of English Men’s 100 League. For that matter, you have quality options available in tonight’s contest.
